240 grams British Beef Mince
120 grams Coleslaw Mix
32 grams Mayonnaise
2 unit(s) Brioche Hot Dog Buns
30 grams Mature Cheddar Cheese
50 grams Gochujang Paste
1 tbsp Honey
2 tbsp Mayonnaise

Heat a frying pan on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, add the beef mince. Fry, 5-6 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.
Break it up as it cooks.

Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the coleslaw mix, mayo and a drizzle of oil.
Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.
Slice the buns top down through the middle (but not all the way through).
Grate the cheese.

Drain the fat from the beef. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle.
Stir in the gochujang and honey (see pantry).
Remove from the heat.

Share the buns between your plates.
Drizzle the mayo inside (see pantry), then fill with the gochujang beef.
Sprinkle over the cheese.
Serve the slaw alongside.
Enjoy!